      },
      {
        "id": "docling_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_083_9",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "ominated by snow-capped Mount Etna, blessed with abundant sunshine and unspoilt landscapes and coastlines, Sicily is a truly beautiful part of Italy, but with a character all of its own. Ruled by different civilisations for millennia, there are countless architectural and archaeological riches to explore, from Piazza Armerina's stunning Roman villa, Monreale's cathedral and Agrigento's Valley of the Temples.",
        "bbox": [
          0.05545286047901793,
          0.7688492061886325,
          0.33826247441007656,
          0.8226744185178078
        ],
        "order": 50
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_083_43",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Thay Firsty Lake Gar da, where wanes lap finesy on the shing them shoreline, with the snow-capped Dolomite mountains in the background; then Venice, a unique city full of cultural delights such as the Doge's Palace, St Mark's Basilica and the Grand Canal; lastly, Verona, one of the most romantic cities you will ever find.",
        "bbox": [
          0.5101663611244848,
          0.7688492066293716,
          0.7837338305575855,
          0.8226744183724588
        ],
        "order": 51
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_083_20",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Relax and unwind whilst soaking up the views of Taormina over an aperitivo Enjoy a boat trip to explore the caves of Syracuse and admire beautiful Ortigia from a different perspective",
        "bbox": [
          0.35120148104258536,
          0.7891865081038592,
          0.47319778263578793,
          0.8605342045425612
        ],
        "order": 52
